    "reasoning": "Three consecutive integers sum to 27: Let m be the middle integer, so m-1, m, m+1 sum to 3m = 27, hence m = 9. Then p = m - 177/20 = 9 - 177/20 = 3/20. Given x% of 60 is 12, we have (x/100)*60 = 12, solving gives x = 20. Now, 100(p)% of x means 100p percent of x. Since p = 3/20, 100p = 15, so 15% of x = 20 is (15/100)*20 = 3. Alternatively, directly p*x = (3/20)*20 = 3.",
